# Server Startup Walkthrough

I have successfully started all the servers for the Yogabuddy/OneBreath application.

## Access Points

| Service | URL | Status |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Web App** | [http://localhost:5003](http://localhost:5003) | ✅ Online |
| **Yoga API** | [http://localhost:5002](http://localhost:5002) | ✅ Online |
| **TTS Backend** | [http://localhost:5001](http://localhost:5001) | ✅ Online |

## Servers Running

The following servers were started using the [start_all_servers.sh](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/Yogabuddy/start_all_servers.sh) script:

1.  **TTS Backend**: Port 5001 (Python)
2.  **Yoga API Server**: Port 5002 (Python/Flask)
3.  **Web App**: Port 5003 (Vite/React)

To stop the servers, you can run the following command in your terminal:
```bash
kill $(lsof -t -i:5001 -i:5002 -i:5003)
```
or find the process running [start_all_servers.sh](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/Yogabuddy/start_all_servers.sh) and interrupt it.
